[How to run]

0. Copy the original source code of B-Prolog into the directory `Emulator'

1. Run bp4prism-modify.sh to create the source code for bp4prism 

    ./bp4prism-modify.sh

2. Move to Emulator.prism and build the libraries for bp4prism
   (platforms: linux32, linux64, darwin9, darwin10, win32 and cygwin)

3. Apply a patch for the final header files

    ./bp4prism-release.sh

